WEEK 6 ANSWERS
6. The Evolution of Modern Medicine:
The field of medicine has come a long way from its ancient roots. Advances in scientific understanding, technology, and medical practices have revolutionized patient care. From the discovery of antibiotics to the development of precision medicine and gene editing, each breakthrough has improved our ability to diagnose, treat, and prevent diseases. However, challenges remain, including equitable access to healthcare and the ongoing battle against emerging infectious diseases.
